text: The great place to immerse yourself into natural hot spring water. Located in the middle of rice fields with the mountain panoramic view will spoil you to enjoy this ancient Hindu's temple. Two medium pools with warm clear water are perfect to enjoy during the rainy season. The entrance ticket is very reasonable less than 10.000 IDR. The only things that the management should improve are the cleanliness of the area, the toilets and the changing rooms. A small cafe is inside the area and some are just near by the entrance gate. Perfect to visit in the morning .

This is an ancient temple with natural warm water exist for centuries. We have to be grateful having ancestors with high sense of art. We just need to keep it well maintained. We hope the government should take some actions to reserve this historical place, by restoration and renovation.

Overall I like this heritage place and want to be back here next time.

name: Trevor Robinson
text: Situs Liyangan has a small Information Centre and doesn't have huge crowds. It does, however, have some excavated relics on show and the future potential of this site is huge. Once it has been properly excavated the sites area has been estimated to be larger than the famous Candi Borobudur. Situs Liyangan is a short distance from Candi Jumprit, coffee and tea plantations plus some awesome vantage points to enjoy some breathtaking local scenery. Trust me, it's well worth a visit.

name: Irtati Hasan Wibisono
text: The road to up is winding and narrow and you have to continue walking from the end road up about 1.5 km. The view however is breathtaking. The temple itself was being reconstructed. Even than the view for me is far more important to see, not to mention friendly natives I met along the walk. I was struggling for the bathroom and one neighbor let me in just like that. Parking is very limited, if possible go with a local driver so you don’t have to worry about parking.
title: Selogriyo Temple

address: H5G9+43R, Hutan, Windusari, Kec. Windusari, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56152, Indonesia
name: andreas aan sugiarto
text: I was amazed by the stunning sceneries along the way to this temple. So green and yet so tranquil. The road for motorbike and pedestrians are well made and maintained. I could not describe more how beautiful this area. And this tiny temple is worth it . On top of the hill ,just if we are lucky enough to enjoy when the sky is clear. Mount Sumbing is the view that we can not miss at all. Parking lot for motorbike is upstair just near to the stairs to the temple but for the car you need to park a little bit far and then you can either walk or take rental bike that costs 25.000 IDR for one way or 40.000 for returns. Toilet is available near by the second gate just before the temple. And it is clean enough. Perfect timing to visit is during dry season ( April to October) or morning when it is not cloudy. I am sure I will be back here to take more pictures.
title: Selogriyo Temple

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: oki nugroho
text:
Situs arkeologi paling menarik saat ini karena kompleksitas yg ditemukan
Bahkan sisa padi/beras yang terbakar pun ditemukan dengan jelas
Dengan beberapa sisa bakaran yang diperkirakan adalah tiang bangunan kayu dan dinding bambu yg sudah tertimbun endapan vulkanik letusan gunung sindoro
Yg paling menarik, bahkan jalan trasahan batu jaman kuno pun ditemukan utuh
Ini luar biasa
Sayangnya sudah 2 th ini proyek liyangan terhenti/dihentikan, padahal besar harapan banyak kejutan dan cerita yang ditemukan lagi
textTranslated:
The most interesting archaeological site today because of the complexity found
Even the remains of burnt paddy/rice were clearly found
With some burnt remains which are thought to be wooden building poles and bamboo walls that have been buried in volcanic sediment from the eruption of Mount Sindoro.
The most interesting thing is that even the ancient stone tram roads were found intact
This is amazing
Unfortunately, it has been 2 years since the Liyangan project has been stalled/discontinued, even though there is high hope that many more surprises and stories will be discovered
title: Situs Liyangan

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Owner Pustaka Druzhba
text: Situs Liyangan, pertama kali mendengar nama ini terlintas dari hasil riset arkeologi disekitar tahun 2009. Situs ini sendiri pernah ditayangkan dan diulas dalam video YouTube Asisi Channel. Foto yang ada pada ulasan saya ini diambil pada tanggal 22 Oktober 2023, pas banget dengan perayaan Hari Santri Nasional. Sebelum datang kesini bayangan saya situs ini sangatlah megah besar dan fantastis, namun nampaknya ekspetasi saya terlalu berlebihan. Situs ini memang memungkinkan adanya relung² sejarah di masa lampau, mengingat lokasinya berdekatan dengan dua gunung suci yaitu Sumbing dan Sindoro, namun sayangnya rekonstruksinya belum sempurna dan nampaknya memang susah untuk direkontruksi, sehingga harus menggunakan wawasan imajiner. Sebelum anda mendatangi situs ini pastikan membawa perlengkapan seperti jaket dan payung, dikarenakan situs ini mirip lapangan terbuka yang sangat luas dan sangat panas, di siang hari anda akan langsung disambut dengan terik matahari yang sangat menyengat. Singkatnya nilai untuk situs ini adalah 8/10, mengingat cukup curam dan terjalnya akses menuju situs ini.. wajib banget deh dikunjungi ketika main ke Temanggung
textTranslated: Liyangan Site, the first time I heard this name came from the results of archaeological research around 2009. This site itself was shown and reviewed in the Asisi Channel YouTube video. The photos in my review were taken on October 22 2023, which is perfect for celebrating National Santri Day. Before coming here, I imagined this site to be very majestic, big and fantastic, but it seems my expectations were too high. This site does allow for historical recesses in the past, considering its location close to two sacred mountains, namely Sumbing and Sindoro, but unfortunately the reconstruction is not perfect and it seems difficult to reconstruct, so you have to use imaginary insight. Before you visit this site, make sure you bring equipment such as a jacket and umbrella, because this site is like a very wide open field and very hot, during the day you will immediately be greeted by the very hot sun. In short, the score for this site is 8/10, considering that it is quite steep and steep to access this site... it is really a must visit when going to Temanggung

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: galih akademik
text: Situa Liyangan di Ds Purbasari Ngadirejo Temanggung ditemukan 2008, dan sd sekarang masih dalam tahap penggalian lanjutan. Situs ini peninggalan Mdang/Mataram Kuno dengan luasan 4 ha lebih ditemukan artefak, lingga yoni unik dengan 3 lubang, candi, persinggahan, kolam, dan jalan batu lebar. Diperkirakan dulu merupakan sentra keagamaan dan permukiman besar yang hancur terkena letusan Gunung Sindoro. Bahkan menurut saksi mata ditemukan rumah kayu utuh yang telah menjadi fosil, tetapi sekarang sudah hancur, ataupun fosil kayu disini. Menurut warga banyak artefak dan candi ditemukan di rumahnya, bahkan bila digali lebih lanjut, jalan batu sudah menuju ujung dusun dan sebagian besar desa bisa masuk dalam zona penggalian. Kondisi saat ini masih banyak tersebar yoni dan benteng batu di sawah dan kebun sekitarnya, penggalian juga masih berlanjut. #literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter @galih.wib
textTranslated: Situa Liyangan in Ds Purbasari Ngadirejo Temanggung was discovered in 2008, and is currently still in the advanced excavation stage. This site is a legacy of Ancient Mdang/Mataram with an area of ​​more than 4 ha where artifacts were found, a unique phallus yoni with 3 holes, a temple, a stopover, a pond and a wide stone path. It is estimated that it used to be a religious center and large settlement that was destroyed by the eruption of Mount Sindoro. In fact, according to eyewitnesses, intact wooden houses were found that had become fossilized, but are now destroyed, or fossilized wood here. According to residents, many artifacts and temples were found in their houses, even if they were dug further, the stone road would have led to the end of the hamlet and most of the village could be included in the excavation zone. The current condition is that there are still many yoni and stone forts scattered in the rice fields and surrounding gardens, excavations are still continuing. #literasyikgalih #kilasdocumenter @galih.wib

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Baihaqi Aditya
text:
06-11-2021

Tapak jejak peradaban penulis pada hari ini bermula dari kota kecil Temanggung. Di suatu titik tinggi di kawasan ini, cerita tentang perkampungan kuno yang sarat dengan spiritualitas mengisi relung sejarah. Peninggalan lebih dari seribu tahun lalu, tatkala gema dinasti Sanjaya dan Syailendra masih masih membunyikan lonceng kejayaannya di Pulau Jawa. Keberadaan Situs Liyangan menjadi serpihan tersembunyi diantaranya.

Menempati area latar berumput luas di Dusun Liyangan, Desa Purbosari, Kecamatan Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung. Keberadaan Situs bersejarah dari zaman kejayaan Hindu klasik ini cukup menantang untuk diakses. Melalui jalanan yang mendaki diantara rumah-rumah penduduk khas pegunungan. Cukup melelahkan memang. Akan tetapi begitu sampai di tujuan, terbayar sudah rasa keingintahuan. Aplikasi Google Maps banyak memberikan kontribusi juga dalam penempatan titik lokasi spot bersejarah ini sehingga secara teknis mudah untuk ditemukan.

Jam menunjukkan pukul 10.30 WIB tatkala rombongan penulis sampai ditempat ini. Datar, bukit tanggul yang tanah merahnya terlihat dari bawah, reruntuhan bebatuan-sebagian membentuk 'candi mini', dan tentu udara sejuk yang menerpa kulit. Itu yang penulis lihat dan rasakan.

Sebagai penikmat sejarah, kisah sisa-sisa perkampungan kuno yang masih menjejak menjadi hal menarik tersendiri. Menurut penuturan 'local guide' yang baru saja selesai melakukan ekskavasi, dikisahkan bahwa pengaruh Kerajaan Mataram Kuno periode awal menyentuh wilayah di kaki Gunung Sindoro ini. Disini diutuslah bebetapa pertapa Hindu untuk mendirikan perkampungan lengkap dengan sarana-prasarana peribadatannya. Candi mini dengan kanal kecil yang menyerupai kolam pemandian atau penyucian menjadi buktinya. Ada pula semacam lumbung penyimpanan padi yang sudah membatu akibat bencana alam dan aktivitas vulkanis. Beberapa tuturan lisan berdasarkan fakta sejarah tersebut tentu semakin menambah khasanah ke-histori-an yang penulis miliki.

Fasilitas pendukung untuk wisatawan dapat dikatakan masih minim. Hanya terdapat dua toilet umum. Itu pun menyatu dengan rumah mess para pekerja arkeologi yang sepertinya ditugaskan di tempat ini. Deretan kios toko yang buka pun hanya ada satu.

Tempat bersejarah ini memang potensial, akan tetapi masih butuh banyak perhatian.

Ancient village ruins in feet of Sindoro Mountains. It believed stand since Hindus Mataram Kingdom about 5 AD. There are paddy granary ruins and pure-pond hindus temple mataram style alike. Potential to be history instagramable spot but still need improved.
textTranslated:
11-06-2021

The author's traces of civilization today begin in the small town of Temanggung. At a high point in this area, stories about ancient villages filled with spirituality fill the historical niche. A relic from more than a thousand years ago, when the echoes of the Sanjaya and Syailendra dynasties were still ringing the bells of their glory on the island of Java. The existence of the Liyangan Site is a hidden fragment of this.

Occupies a large grassy background area in Liyangan Hamlet, Purbosari Village, Ngadirejo District, Temanggung Regency. The existence of this historical site from the glorious era of classical Hinduism is quite challenging to access. Through roads that climb between typical mountain houses. It's quite tiring indeed. However, once you arrive at your destination, your curiosity pays off. The Google Maps application has also contributed a lot in locating these historic spots so that they are technically easy to find.

The clock showed 10.30 WIB when the writing group arrived at this place. Flat, embanked hills whose red soil is visible from below, rock ruins - some of which form 'mini temples', and of course the cool air that hits your skin. That's what the author saw and felt.

As a history lover, the story of the remains of ancient villages that are still traced is interesting in itself. According to a local guide who has just finished carrying out excavations, it is said that the influence of the ancient Mataram Kingdom in the early period touched this area at the foot of Mount Sindoro. Here several Hindu ascetics were sent to build a village complete with facilities and infrastructure for worship. The mini temple with a small canal that resembles a bathing or cleansing pool is proof of this. There is also a kind of rice storage barn that has been petrified due to natural disasters and volcanic activity. Several oral narratives based on historical facts certainly add to the author's historical repertoire.

Supporting facilities for tourists can be said to be still minimal. There are only two public toilets. It is also attached to the mess house for archaeological workers who seem to be assigned to this place. Only one row of shop stalls was open.

This historic place has potential, but still needs a lot of attention.

Ancient village ruins at the feet of Sindoro Mountains. It is believed to stand since the Hindu Mataram Kingdom about 5 AD. There are paddy granary ruins and pure-pond Hindu temple Mataram style alike. Potential to be a historical instagramable spot but still needs improvement.

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: agus nugroho
text:
Situs Liyangan terdapat di dusun Liyangan, kelurahan Purbosari, kecamatan Ngadirejo, kabupaten Temanggung. Adalah pemukiman peradaban manusia kuno nenek moyang kita, dimana terdapat dan ditemukan sebuah punden berundak, talut, latar, kayu, area pertanian, tempat peribadatan, dan sisa bekas pembakaran.
Banyak benda yang sudah ditemukan dan memang sengaja di kubur kembali agar tidak terkikis oleh air hujan.
Mungkin peradaban masa lampau yang masih kental dengan agama hindu.
Masih banyak benda sejarah masa lampau yang masih terkubur dan belum terungkap, dimana dibagian sisi selatan yang masih melakukan penggalian.
Bukti sejarah peradaban manusia masa lampau yang terkubur dalam sekitar 15meter tersebut bisa menjadi destinasi wisata sejarah.
Terima kasih buat Badan arkeolog yogyakarta yang berperan aktif mengungkap temuan tersebut.
Sungguh kaya akan sejarah di bumi Indonesia.
textTranslated:
The Liyangan site is located in Liyangan hamlet, Purbosari sub-district, Ngadirejo sub-district, Temanggung district. It is a settlement of ancient human civilization of our ancestors, where there were and were found punden terraces, talut, backdrop, wood, agricultural areas, places of worship, and remains from burning.
Many objects have been found and were deliberately reburied so that they would not be eroded by rainwater.
Maybe past civilizations were still strongly influenced by Hinduism.
There are still many historical objects from the past that are still buried and have not been revealed, where excavations are still being carried out on the south side.
Historical evidence of past human civilization buried around 15 meters deep could become a historical tourist destination.
Thank you to the Yogyakarta Archaeological Agency who played an active role in uncovering these findings.
Indonesia's history is truly rich.
title: Situs Liyangan

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: windu dolandolan
text: Situs liyangan sebuah situs luwar biyasa yg terletak di utara lereng gunung sindoro. Situs i i masih sangat mejadi misteri dan menimbulkan pertanyaan besar 'ini situs apa?' Dengan kontur miring khas gunung yang berteras-teras dan memiliki banagur yang di atasnya terdapat yoninlubang 3, lalu juga terdapat petirtaan, jalan kuno, bangunan dari kayi, dll. Pokoknya buanyak dan masoh menjadi kisteri.
textTranslated: The Liyangan site is a Luwar Biyasa site located on the northern slopes of Mount Sindoro. This site is still very much a mystery and raises the big question 'what site is this?' With the typical sloping contours of a mountain that has terraces and has a banagur on top of which there is Yonin Lubang 3, then there are also Lightning, ancient roads, wooden buildings, etc. Anyway, there are lots of them and they still become a mystery.
title: Situs Liyangan

address: Dusun Liyangan, Area Sawah, Purbosari, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Hadi
text:

Bila kebanyakan candi digunakan sebagai tempat pemujaan, maka komplek ini merupakan tempat hunian. Fungsinya hampir mirip seperti keraton Boko.
Lokasinya di kaki gunung menjadikan terasa sangat sejuk...
textTranslated:
An important site of Javanese civilization. The site was used as an ancient Javanese residential complex.
If most temples are used as places of worship, then this complex is a residential area. Its function is almost the same as the Boko palace.
Its location at the foot of the mountain makes it feel very cool...

Tempat dimana ditemukannya jejak sejarah peradaban manusia di lereng Gunung Sindoro pada abad 2 sampai abad 11.
Situs ini menarik sekali karena terdiri dari 3 Komplek, yaitu komplek Pemukiman,komplek peribadatan, komplek pertanian.
textTranslated:
The place where traces of the history of human civilization were found on the slopes of Mount Sindoro from the 2nd to the 11th centuries.
This site is very interesting because it consists of 3 complexes, namely a residential complex, a worship complex, and an agricultural complex.

text: Komplek Candi Liyangan diperkirakan merupakan pemukiman Hindu sebelum abad ke-10 Masehi. Luas komplek situs wilayah lebih dari satu hektare dan berada di area penambangan batu. Penemuan situs ini berasal dari warga saat mereka menambang batu dan menemukan runtuhan Candi. Sangat disarankan untuk mengunjungi Candi Liyangan karena pemandangannya sangat bagus dan bisa belajar banyak mengenai pemukiman Klasik pada masa lalu. Selain itu, pengunjung bisa bertanya kepada juru pelihara Candi mengenai sejarah Candi Liyangan, mereka akan bersenang hati untuk menjelaskan.
textTranslated: The Liyangan Temple Complex is thought to have been a Hindu settlement before the 10th century AD. The area of ​​the regional site complex is more than one hectare and is located in a stone mining area. The discovery of this site came from residents when they were mining stone and found the ruins of a temple. It is highly recommended to visit Liyangan Temple because the views are very beautiful and you can learn a lot about Classical settlements in the past. Apart from that, visitors can ask the temple keepers about the history of Liyangan Temple, they will be happy to explain.

name: bejo infomitigasi
text:
Situs Liyangan Temanggung: Jendela Peradaban Mataram Kuno
Situs Liyangan, yang terletak di Dusun Liyangan, Desa Purbosari, Kecamatan Ngadirejo, Temanggung, Jawa Tengah, merupakan salah satu situs arkeologi terpenting di Indonesia. Situs ini diperkirakan merupakan bekas permukiman masyarakat Mataram Kuno yang kompleks dan lengkap, dengan berbagai peninggalan bersejarah yang masih terawat. Berikut beberapa informasi penting tentang Situs Liyangan:
Sejarah Penemuan:
* Ditemukan secara resmi pada tahun 2008, meskipun laporan penemuan artefak di area tersebut sudah ada sebelumnya.
* Penemuan situs ini diawali dari kegiatan penambangan pasir yang menemukan struktur bangunan.
Keunikan Situs Liyangan:
* Menyimpan sisa-sisa kayu dan bijian serealia (gabah) yang hangus, hal yang jarang ditemukan di situs Hindu Jawa lainnya.
* Menunjukkan bukti adanya sistem pertanian terstruktur pada masa pra-Hindu.
* Diperkirakan menjadi cikal bakal Kerajaan Mataram Kuno.
Peninggalan Bersejarah:
* Sisa-sisa bangunan tempat tinggal, candi, dan struktur lainnya.
* Artefak seperti gerabah, peralatan batu, dan perhiasan.
* Bukti sistem irigasi dan pertanian.
Status dan Nilai Penting:
* Diusulkan untuk dijadikan Cagar Budaya Nasional.
* Memiliki nilai penting untuk memahami sejarah dan budaya Mataram Kuno.
* Menjadi potensi wisata edukasi dan penelitian arkeologi.
Akses dan Fasilitas:
* Situs Liyangan dapat diakses dengan mudah dari Kota Temanggung.
* Tersedia fasilitas seperti museum, taman arkeologi, dan pemandu wisata.
Tips Berkunjung:
* Gunakan pakaian dan alas kaki yang nyaman.
* Bawalah topi dan air minum.
* Patuhi peraturan dan jaga kelestarian situs.
textTranslated:
Liyangan Temanggung Site: A Window on Ancient Mataram Civilization
The Liyangan site, located in Liyangan Hamlet, Purbosari Village, Ngadirejo District, Temanggung, Central Java, is one of the most important archaeological sites in Indonesia. This site is thought to be a complex and complete former settlement of the Ancient Mataram community, with various historical relics that are still well preserved. Here is some important information about the Liyangan Site:
Discovery History:
*Officially discovered in 2008, although reports of artifacts being discovered in the area date back before that.
* The discovery of this site began with sand mining activities that discovered building structures.
Uniqueness of the Liyangan Site:
* Stores charred remains of wood and cereal grains (grain), something that is rarely found at other Javanese Hindu sites.
* Shows evidence of the existence of a structured agricultural system in pre-Hindu times.
* Estimated to be the forerunner of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom.
Historical item:
* Remains of residential buildings, temples and other structures.
* Artifacts such as pottery, stone tools, and jewelry.
* Evidence of irrigation and agricultural systems.
Important Status and Values:
* Proposed to be made a National Cultural Heritage.
* Has important value for understanding the history and culture of Ancient Mataram.
* Has the potential for educational tourism and archaeological research.
Access and Facilities:
* The Liyangan site can be accessed easily from Temanggung City.
* Facilities such as museums, archaeological parks and tour guides are available.
Visiting Tips:
* Wear comfortable clothing and footwear.
* Bring a hat and drinking water.
* Comply with regulations and maintain site sustainability.

title: Selogriyo Temple

address: H5G9+43R, Hutan, Windusari, Kec. Windusari, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56152, Indonesia
name: Banyubiru Putra
text:
Banyak wisatawan asing bilang kalau tempat ini lebih indah dari UBUD BALI. Jadi pemandangan menuju ke candi ini sangat menyegarkan mata!!

Namun perlu dinote bahwa jalan ini hanya bisa diakses dengan jalan kaki atau motor, jarak tempat parkir menuju candi sekitar 2-3KM.

Tempat sekeliling candi cukup bersih dan tertata, nah pas jalan menuju candi ada 1 buah kedai kopi dan teh yang rasanya cukup syahdu dengan harga bersahabat. Kalau untuk makanan seinget saya ada snack dan mie instan.

Kalau mau kesini mending pagi atau sore jam 15.00 biar g panas dan kalau kemaleman ga ada penerangan lampu.
textTranslated:
Many foreign tourists say that this place is more beautiful than UBUD, BALI. So the view towards this temple is very refreshing for the eyes!!

However, it should be noted that this road can only be accessed by foot or motorbike, the distance from the parking lot to the temple is around 2-3KM.

The area around the temple is quite clean and orderly, and on the way to the temple there is a coffee and tea shop which tastes quite delicious and has friendly prices. As for food, as far as I remember, there were snacks and instant noodles.

If you want to come here, it's better to come here in the morning or afternoon at 15.00 so it's not hot and if it's late at night there's no lights.
title: Selogriyo Temple

address: H5G9+43R, Hutan, Windusari, Kec. Windusari, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56152, Indonesia
name: Asep Prastyo
text:
Candi Selogriyo terletak di lokasi yang cukup terpencil di lereng Gunung Giyanti, dikelilingi oleh pemandangan alam yang indah. Perjalanan menuju candi ini melibatkan trekking melalui sawah terasering dan perbukitan hijau, memberikan pengalaman yang menenangkan dan menyegarkan bagi para pengunjung. Pemandangan dari candi ini sangat menakjubkan, terutama saat cuaca cerah, dengan latar belakang pegunungan dan hamparan sawah yang luas.

Candi Selogriyo diperkirakan dibangun pada masa Mataram Kuno, sekitar abad ke-8 hingga 9 Masehi. Meskipun ukurannya kecil, candi ini memiliki detail arsitektur yang menarik, dengan ukiran yang masih terlihat jelas pada bagian dinding dan relief. Candi ini dibangun dari batu andesit, yang menambah keunikan dan nilai sejarahnya. Bagi penggemar sejarah dan arkeologi, Candi Selogriyo menawarkan wawasan tentang peradaban kuno di Jawa Tengah.

Untuk mencapai Candi Selogriyo, pengunjung harus menempuh perjalanan trekking yang memakan waktu sekitar 30-45 menit dari tempat parkir. Jalur trekking ini cukup mudah dan bisa diakses oleh pemula, namun tetap menantang karena melintasi beberapa medan berbukit. Trekking ini memberikan pengalaman yang menyenangkan karena pengunjung akan melewati area persawahan, hutan kecil, dan sungai-sungai kecil. Jalur yang asri dan sejuk membuat perjalanan menuju candi ini terasa singkat.

Candi Selogriyo tidak seramai candi-candi besar lainnya seperti Borobudur atau Prambanan, sehingga pengunjung bisa menikmati suasana yang lebih tenang dan damai. Tempat ini cocok bagi mereka yang mencari ketenangan atau ingin bermeditasi di tempat yang dikelilingi oleh alam. Kehadiran candi di tengah alam memberikan kesan spiritual yang mendalam.

Candi Selogriyo cukup terawat meskipun lokasinya yang terpencil. Area sekitar candi bersih dan tertata dengan baik, menunjukkan perhatian yang baik dari pihak pengelola dan masyarakat setempat dalam menjaga warisan budaya ini.

Waktu terbaik untuk mengunjungi Candi Selogriyo adalah pada pagi hari atau sore hari untuk menghindari terik matahari dan menikmati suasana yang lebih sejuk. Selain itu, berkunjung di musim kemarau akan memberikan pengalaman trekking yang lebih nyaman karena medan yang lebih kering.

Secara keseluruhan, Candi Selogriyo adalah destinasi yang menarik bagi pecinta sejarah, arsitektur, dan alam. Meskipun ukuran dan skalanya lebih kecil dibandingkan candi-candi lainnya di Jawa Tengah, pengalaman yang ditawarkan oleh Candi Selogriyo tidak kalah menarik, terutama karena lokasinya yang asri dan pemandangan alam yang indah.
textTranslated:
Selogriyo Temple is located in a quite remote location on the slopes of Mount Giyanti, surrounded by beautiful natural scenery. The journey to the temple involves trekking through terraced rice fields and green hills, providing a calming and refreshing experience for visitors. The view from this temple is amazing, especially in clear weather, with a backdrop of mountains and vast expanses of rice fields.

Selogriyo Temple is thought to have been built during the Ancient Mataram period, around the 8th to 9th centuries AD. Despite its small size, this temple has interesting architectural details, with carvings that are still clearly visible on the walls and reliefs. This temple was built from andesite stone, which adds to its uniqueness and historical value. For history and archeology fans, Selogriyo Temple offers insight into ancient civilization in Central Java.

To reach Selogriyo Temple, visitors must take a trekking trip which takes around 30-45 minutes from the parking lot. This trekking route is quite easy and can be accessed by beginners, but it is still challenging because it crosses some hilly terrain. This trekking provides a pleasant experience because visitors will pass through rice fields, small forests and small rivers. The beautiful and cool path makes the journey to this temple feel short.

Selogriyo Temple is not as busy as other large temples such as Borobudur or Prambanan, so visitors can enjoy a calmer and more peaceful atmosphere. This place is suitable for those who are looking for tranquility or want to meditate in a place surrounded by nature. The presence of a temple in the middle of nature gives a deep spiritual impression.

Selogriyo Temple is quite well maintained despite its remote location. The area around the temple is clean and well-organized, showing good attention from the management and local community in maintaining this cultural heritage.

The best time to visit Selogriyo Temple is in the morning or evening to avoid the hot sun and enjoy a cooler atmosphere. Apart from that, visiting in the dry season will provide a more comfortable trekking experience because the terrain is drier.

Overall, Selogriyo Temple is an interesting destination for history, architecture and nature lovers. Even though its size and scale are smaller than other temples in Central Java, the experience offered by Selogriyo Temple is no less interesting, especially because of its beautiful location and beautiful natural views.

In the language, Selogriyo Temple means, Selo = stone, Griya = house, meaning a house made of stone. Mythologically, Selogriyo Temple is a picture of Mount Mahameru, where the gods reside. Selogriyo Temple is located on the slopes of Mount Sumbing under Giyanti Hill and Cindong Hill.

There is 1 temple, there is a phallus and yoni too like most temples.  The place is not very large but the view is very beautiful. The place is clean and well maintained, there are only a few traces of fandalism around the temple :(

Selogriyo Temple and its surroundings are used as a tracking route for local and foreign tourists, because the view from the ticket window to the temple is very beautiful.

Maybe in the future Selogriyo temple tourism can be further developed, the local government can collaborate with local communities in developing facilities around the temple.

Untuk akses sendiri pengunjung harus berjalan kaki melalui jalan setapak selebar 1 meter yang membelah area persawahan dan jalanan menanjak. Untuk itu saya sarankan siapkan fisik yang kuat dan membawa perbekalan minuman dan makanan.

It is said that this temple was built during the heyday of Hinduism in the 8th century AD. Located at the top of a hill, the location of Selogriyo Temple can be said to be quite remote. The location around the temple is quite lush and cool because it is at an altitude of ±740 meters above sea level.

To access themselves, visitors must walk along a 1 meter wide footpath that divides the rice fields and uphill roads. For this reason, I suggest being physically strong and bringing supplies of drinks and food.

name: Zero Hunter
text:
Candi Selogriyo adalah sebuah peninggalan purbakala di Kecamatan Windusari, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah. Candi ini diperkirakan dibangun pada abad ke-9 M, pada masa Kerajaan Mataram Kuno. Arsitektur Indonesia Klasik berlatar belakang agama Hindu ini menghadap ke arah timur. Di empat sisi dinding bangunan candi terdapat lima relung tempat arca-arca perwujudan dewa. Arca-arca tersebut adalah Durga Mahisasuramardini (dinding utara), Ganesha (dinding barat), Agastya (dinding selatan), serta Nandiswara dan Mahakala (dinding timur). Salah satu keistimewaan candi tanpa perwara ini adalah kemuncaknya yang berbentuk buah keben. Kemuncak tersebut disebut amalaka.
Pada bulan Desember 1998, candi ini hancur karena bukit tempat bangunan berdiri mengalami kelongsoran. Proses rekonstruksi ulang selesai dilakukan pada tahun 2005.

Sc: Wikipedia
textTranslated:
Selogriyo Temple is an ancient relic in Windusari District, Magelang Regency, Central Java. This temple is thought to have been built in the 9th century AD, during the time of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom. Classical Indonesian architecture with a Hindu religious background faces east. On the four sides of the walls of the temple building there are five niches where statues of god's embodiment are placed. The statues are Durga Mahisasuramardini (north wall), Ganesha (west wall), Agastya (south wall), and Nandiswara and Mahakala (east wall). One of the features of this temple without perwara is its peak which is in the shape of a keben fruit. The peak is called amalaka.
In December 1998, this temple was destroyed because the hill on which the building stood collapsed. The reconstruction process was completed in 2005.

Sc: Wikipedia

textTranslated: It's called Umbul Temple, but you won't find any temple buildings inside. There are only two bathing pools with lukewarm water which is said to be able to cure various skin diseases. Soaking here is very enjoyable because it's not too crowded with visitors. The atmosphere is serene because it's located in the middle of rice fields. and hills.
title: Umbul Temple

address: J7RW+5R7, Jl. Candi Umbul, Perkebunan, Kartoharjo, Kec. Grabag, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56196, Indonesia
name: Ahmad Dzikri Al Kafi
text:
Pemandian Air Hangat Candi Umbul terletak di Desa Kartoharjo, Kecamatan Grabag Kabupaten Magelan ini kian menarik mendukung Borobudur Kabupaten Magelang.  Daya Tarik Wisata budaya ini berbeda dengan dari Candi - Candi lainya, Pemandian Air Hangat Candi Umbul begitu spesial dan unik, kebanyakan candi menjulang naik sepeti piramida tetapi acndi ini dalam bentuk kolam. Berbeda dengan yang lain dari dasar kolam Air Hangat Candi Umbul mengeluarkan gelembung - gelembung air  yang merupakan belerang yang keluar dari dasar kolam mengeluarkan air hangat yang dapt menyembuhkan penyakit kulit.

Seluruh dinding dari batu andesit , seperti batu untuk pembuatan candi-candi  seperti candi Borobobudur , Pawon awon dan lainnya .menurut legenda dari turun menurun nenek moyang dahalu tempat ini dijadikan untuk pemandian para bangsawan di jaman mataram kuno.

Beberapa batuan endesit ditepi kolam ada relief tumbuhan dan binatang dan stupa.beberapa petilasan lingga dan yoni di beberapa titik membuktikan  bahwa candi Umbul merupakan candi bercorak hindu  dan kemungkinan di bangun pada masa Dinasti Sanjaya.

. Pemandian Air Hangat Candi Umbul  terdapat beberapa fasilitas yang bisa kita nikmati seperti  gazebo – gasebo, tempat bilas serta kantin yang dibangun memberikan kenyaman para pengunjung. Bagi pengunjung yang ingin  mengadakan rapat / pertemuan terdapat juga aula outdor dan aula panggung dengan pemandangan alam yang masih alami.

Tarif masuk Pemandian air hangat Candi Umbul

Untuk hari Senin s.d Jumat                       : Rp. 5.500,-

Untuk hari Sabtu, minggu dan Hari libur  : Rp. 6.500,-

Untuk Penggunaan Fasilitas diPemandian Air hangat Candi Umbul ada tarif sewa antara lain:

Untuk Bangunan  (per m2 perbulan ) :  Rp. 150.000

Untuk Lahan  (per m2 perbulan )         :  Rp. 125.000
textTranslated:
The Umbul Temple Warm Springs are located in Kartoharjo Village, Grabag District, Magelan Regency. This is becoming increasingly attractive and supports Borobudur, Magelang Regency.  This cultural tourist attraction is different from other temples, the Umbul Temple Warm Water Bath is very special and unique, most temples rise like pyramids but this temple is in the form of a pool. Different from the others, from the bottom of the pool, the Umbul Temple Warm Water emits water bubbles, which is sulfur that comes out from the bottom of the pool, releasing warm water that can cure skin diseases.

The entire walls are made of andesite stone, like the stone for making temples  such as the Borobobudur temple, Pawon Awon and others. According to legend passed down from generation to generation by our ancestors, this place was used as a bath for nobles in the ancient Mataram era.

Some of the endesite rocks at the edge of the pond have reliefs of plants and animals and stupas. Several glimpses of the phallus and yoni at several points prove  that the Umbul temple is a Hindu style temple  and was probably built during the Sanjaya Dynasty.

. The Umbul Temple Warm Springs  have several facilities that we can enjoy such as  gazebos, a place to rinse and a canteen that was built to provide comfort for visitors. For visitors who want to hold meetings/convocations, there is also an outdoor hall and a stage hall with unspoiled natural views.

Entry fee for Umbul Temple warm springs

For Monday to Friday                       : Rp. 5,500,-

For Saturdays, Sundays and holidays  : Rp. 6,500,-

To use the facilities at Candi Umbul's hot springs, there are rental rates, including:

For Buildings (per m2 per month ) :  Rp. 150,000

For Land (per m2 per month )         :  Rp. 125,000

text:
25 Desember 2023
Situs petirtaan yang baru pertama saya kunjungi yang terdiri dari dua kolam dengan kedalaman air sekitar 120 centimeter dengan air yang berasa hangat - hangat kuku (sekitar 35 derajat Celcius) sehingga efek terapinya kurang, dibandingkan dengan di Air Panas Derekan (Candi Ngempon). Kolam ini memang hanya untuk berendam karena dasar kolam dipenuhi pecahan blok batu - batu andesit penyusun badan candinya.
Biaya masuk IDR 7K / orang dan parkir mobil IDR 5K. Akses menuju Candi Umbul dekat dengan jalan raya Pringsurat Temanggung, yaitu sekitar 1 kilometer namun hanya khusus mobil kecil karena ada dua palang besi di atas jalan dengan ketinggian maksimal 2,2 meter saja.
textTranslated:
December 25, 2023
The first Lightning site I visited consisted of two pools with a water depth of around 120 centimeters with the water feeling lukewarm (around 35 degrees Celsius) so the therapeutic effect was less, compared to Derekan Hot Springs (Ngempon Temple). This pool is only for soaking because the bottom of the pool is filled with broken andesite stone blocks that make up the body of the temple.
Entrance fee IDR 7K / person and car parking IDR 5K. Access to Umbul Temple is close to the Pringsurat Temanggung highway, which is around 1 kilometer but only for small cars because there are two iron bars on the road with a maximum height of only 2.2 meters.
title: Umbul Temple

text:
Pemandian air panas Candi Umbul, tiket masuk Rp6000/orang, parkir motor Rp3000, parkir mobil Rp5000. Kebetulan pas saya kesana, masih pagi jadi air masih bersih. Kata orang, sering kotor soalnya.

Hati2 saat masuk ke dalam kolam, bagian bawahnya adalah batu & berlumut. Ada beberapa batu yang lumayan besar, jadi hati2 tersandung.

Area bilas, hanya ada 1 dari 4 shower yang bisa dipakai. Selain itu rusak. Ruang ganti juga kotor & tidak terawat. Beberapa ruang bau pesing, bahkan lampunya pada hilang. Ada pula yang tidak bisa dikunci.

Aneh kan, fasilitas utama dari pemandian kan ruang bilas & ganti, tapi ini malah tidak terawat sama sekali.
Semoga bisa menjadi masukan & lebih baik lagi kedepannya.
textTranslated:
Umbul Temple hot springs, entrance ticket IDR 6000/person, motorbike parking IDR 3000, car parking IDR 5000. Coincidentally, when I went there, it was still early in the morning so the water was still clean. People say it's often dirty.

Be careful when entering the pool, the bottom is rocky & mossy. There are some quite large rocks, so be careful of tripping.

Rinse area, only 1 of 4 showers can be used. Apart from that it's broken. The changing room is also dirty & unkempt. Some rooms smell of urine, even the lights are missing. There are also those that cannot be locked.

It's strange, isn't it, the main facility of the bath is the rinse & change room, but this is not maintained at all.
Hopefully it can provide input & make it even better in the future.
title: Umbul Temple

name: Agatha Theodora
text:
Letaknya di daerah Grabag, Magelang. Ditemukan situs dengan sumber air hangat di daerah ini, kemudian dibuka untuk umum. Tidak bau tp tetap mengandung belerang. Airnya sedikit keruh shg wajib bilas setelah mandi di sini. Kolamnya kecil, airnya hangat (tdk panas). Tiket Rp5.000 per orang, parkir motor 2.000.

Yang sangat disayangkan, tempat bilas perempuan tidak berfungsi showernya. Ada pancuran yg berfungsi tp di luar. Kamar ganti dan toilet kuncinya rusak semua. Di jam-jam tertentu ramai orang dan bahkan ada yang mandi pakai shampoo/sabun di dalam kolam. Mengganggu pengunjung lainnya.
textTranslated:
It is located in the Grabag area, Magelang. A site with warm water sources was discovered in this area, then it was opened to the public. It doesn't smell but still contains sulfur. The water is a little cloudy so you have to rinse after bathing here. The pool is small, the water is warm (not hot). Tickets IDR 5,000 per person, motorbike parking IDR 2,000.

What's very unfortunate is that the women's toilet doesn't have a functioning shower. There is a functioning shower but it is outside. The changing room and toilet locks were all broken. At certain hours there are lots of people and some people even bathe using shampoo/soap in the pool. Disturbing other visitors.
title: Umbul Temple

Kalau kesini bawa pakaian ganti dan pakaian renang ya,

Sampah plastik buang ditempat sampah !

JAGALAH KEBERSIHAN KEBERSIHAN SEBAGIAN DARI KEMANUSIAAN.
textTranslated:
There is a place to change clothes, there are toilets, men and women are separated. There is 1 queue for each 😁 there is a canteen too.

Remains of the ancient Javanese King's bath.

Ticket price IDR 6,000 per person
Car parking price IDR 5,000 per car⁸

When entering the location, there is a pretty good garden but there is land that is not used.
There is a gazebo provided to relax and enjoy the surrounding views.
There is an adult pool and a children's pool, the pool is not too big and the depth of the adult pool is stomach level.
Normal warm water is not hot, quite clear but lots of moss.

To rinse the room, if the floor is not maintained, many doors are dirty, many doors are damaged, and many faucets are also damaged.

text: Akhirnya ke Candi ini setelah penasaran bertahun-tahun karena cerita dari masa kecil Ibu yang kalau kesini harus nyebrang sungai progo dan mbelah hutan. Saya naik motor ke sini, dari magelang arah bandongan nanti naik ke daerah pemukiman sampai gapura yang ada loketnya beli tiket lalu menyusuri jalanan kecil yang cukup lumayan kalau ngga pas bawa motornya, usahakan motor yang bisa untuk tanjakan dan pastikan motornya remnya pakem,  sekitar sekilo sampai ke parkiran candi.  Kalau naik mobil saya kurang tau di mana parkir tapi harus jalan kaki dua kilometer. Dari parkiran tinggal naik tangga 10 menit dan sampai di candinya. Sungguh terawat sekaliiiiiii luarbiasa. Ada warung juga diatas bisa jajan kalau capek. Sungguh menyenangkan wisata sejarah ke candi ini!
textTranslated: Finally went to this temple after being curious for years because of stories from my mother's childhood that if you came here you had to cross the Progo river and cut through the forest. I rode a motorbike here, from Magelang towards Bandongan, then I went up to the residential area to the gate where there was a ticket window, then along the small road which is quite good if you don't fit the motorbike, try to get a motorbike that can go uphill and make sure the motorbike has good brakes, about a kilometer to to the temple parking lot.  If I go by car, I don't know where to park but I have to walk two kilometers. From the parking lot, just go up the stairs for 10 minutes and arrive at the temple. It's really very well maintained. There is also a stall above where you can have a snack if you are tired. What a fun historical tour to this temple!

text: Jalan di desa Liyangan agak sempit, tp masih bisa dilalui mobil. Parkiran cukup besar, ada juga parkiran yg Deket situs Liyangan ada juga yang jalan kaki sekitar 500 meter. Di situs Liyangan nanti bisa dijelaskan sama pemandu disana, baik orangnya dan dijelaskan dengan baik penemuan penemuan yg d temukan d situs Liyangan. Semoga kedepannya makin banyak yg di gali dan d temukan. Merinding banget saya berada d sini karena desa kuno ini udh keren dan maju, ditemukan jalan batu yg lebar sekitar 5 meter dan juga setiap bangunan di kelilingi pagar. Ada pertitaan, ada lumbung padi Oia ada fosil padi juga disini, ada tempat tinggal, dan tempat ibadah juga.
textTranslated: The road in Liyangan village is rather narrow, but still passable by car. The parking lot is quite large, there is also a parking lot near the Liyangan site, there is also a walk of about 500 meters. At the Liyangan site, you can later explain to the guide there, both people and explain well the discoveries found at the Liyangan site. Hopefully in the future more will be dug up and found. I really get goosebumps here because this ancient village is already cool and developed, you can find a stone road that is about 5 meters wide and every building is surrounded by a fence. There is a temple, there is a rice barn. Oh, there are rice fossils here too, there are residences and places of worship too.

When you go there, the atmosphere is quiet because it's cloudy and people are less interested in it. text: Candi Umbul adalah situs purbakala berupa pemandian air panas yang terletak di Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Candi ini dibangun sejak zaman Wangsa Syailendra, dan sampai sekarang sisa-sia peninggalannya masih tetap dilindungi dan dijadikan salah satu objek wisata andalan di Kabupaten Magelang
textTranslated: Umbul Temple is an ancient site in the form of a hot spring located in Magelang Regency, Central Java, Indonesia. This temple was built during the time of the Syailendra dynasty, and until now its remains are still protected and used as one of the main tourist attractions in Magelang Regency.

Tersedia 2 kolam untuk dewasa dan anak-anak.
Kolamnya eksotis khas jaman kerajaan mataram kuno.
Akan lebih eksotis lagi bila kolamnya lebih bersih sehingga tidak ada rasa takut atau khawatir bila pengunjung mau "nyemplung", takut ada binatang /benda berbahaya karena dasar kolam tidak kelihatan.
Fasilitas sudah dibangun hanya butuh pemeliharaan dan penataan agar lebih bersih dan nyaman. Tempat sampah perlu ditambah.
Tempat bilas dan ganti pakaian sudah ada.
textTranslated:
There are 2 pools for adults and children.
The pool is exotic, typical of the ancient Mataram kingdom era.
It will be even more exotic if the pool is cleaner so that there is no fear or worry if visitors want to "plunge in", afraid of dangerous animals/objects because the bottom of the pool is not visible.
The facilities have been built, they just need maintenance and arrangement to make them cleaner and more comfortable. Trash cans need to be added.
There is a place to rinse and change clothes.
title: Umbul Temple

address: J7RW+5R7, Jl. Candi Umbul, Perkebunan, Kartoharjo, Kec. Grabag, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56196, Indonesia
name: Sandi Wibisono
text: Klo dari Temanggung bisa lewat polsek Pringsurat ke kanan tapi karena kami juga mo mampir ke rumah temen di Grabag kami putuskan lewat Krincing ke arah Grabag untuk sampai disini, masuk ke lokasi lewat jalan aspal yang cukup wat 2  🚘🚘 mobil. Lokasi wisatanya tidak terlalu luas, dan masuk kedalam ada 2 kolam pemandian air panas, hawanya di lokasi cukup adem khas pegunungan⛰️ tapi begitu berendam di dalam kolam langsung terasa hangat menyegarkan! Mata airnya💦 berasal dari dasar kolam yang meyembur terus tidak pernah berhenti sambil mengeluarkan gelembung 2 udara yang menarik untuk dilihat, sayang air di kolam tidak terlalu jernih mungkin karena dasarnya lumpur. ✌
textTranslated: From Temanggung you can go via the Pringsurat police station to the right, but because we were also going to stop by a friend's house in Grabag, we decided to go via Krincing towards Grabag to get here, entering the location via an asphalt road which was enough for 2 🚘🚘 cars. The tourist location is not very large, and when you enter there are 2 hot spring pools, the weather at the location is quite cool, typical of the mountains⛰️ but as soon as you soak in the pool you immediately feel refreshingly warm! The spring💦 comes from the bottom of the pool which gushes continuously and never stops while releasing air bubbles which are interesting to look at, unfortunately the water in the pool is not very clear, maybe because the bottom is mud. ✌
title: Umbul Temple

textTranslated: This temple was built in the 8th century AD at the same time as the construction of Kalasan Temple, namely during the reign of Rakai Panangkaran. The connection between these two temples is explained in the Kalasan Inscription (700 years Saka / 778 AD).

text:
Minggu, 4 Agustus 2024.
Candi Sari berada Bendan, Tirtomartani, Kalasan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta­. Candi Sari terletak sekitar 500 meter di sebelah ti­mur laut Candi Kalasan. Kata “sari” berarti cantik atau elok. Penamaan tersebut kemungkinan didasari atas kenyataan bahwa Candi Sari memiliki hiasan serta corak gaya bangunan yang indah.

Candi Sari merupakan sebuah bangunan wihara atau asrama bagi para pendeta. Candi ini berlatar belakang agama Buddha, diperkirakan Candi Sari dibangun sezaman dengan Candi Kalasan, yaitu sekitar abad 8 Masehi.

Candi Sari ditemukan dalam kondisi rusak. Jawatan Purbakala Hindia Belanda memugar Candi Sari pada tahun 1929 – 1930. Hasil pemugaran belum sempurna karena banyak batu-batu penyusun candi yang hilang. Oleh karena itu, batu-batu asli yang tidak ditemukan terpaksa diganti dengan batu polos.
textTranslated:
Sunday, August 4 2024.
Sari Temple is located in Bendan, Tirtomartani, Kalasan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region. Sari Temple is located about 500 meters to the northeast of Kalasan Temple. The word "sari" means beautiful or beautiful. This naming is probably based on the fact that Sari Temple has beautiful decorations and building styles.

Candi Sari is a monastery or dormitory building for priests. This temple has a Buddhist religious background, it is estimated that Sari Temple was built at the same time as Kalasan Temple, namely around the 8th century AD.

Sari Temple was found in a damaged condition. The Dutch East Indies Antiquities Department restored Sari Temple in 1929 – 1930. The results of the restoration were not perfect because many of the stones that made up the temple were missing. Therefore, the original stones that were not found had to be replaced with plain stones.
title: Sari Temple

text: Candi Sari ini aslinya memang merupakan bangunan bertingkat dua atau bahkan tiga. Lantai atas dulunya digunakan untuk menyimpan barang-barang untuk kepentingan keagamaan, sedangkan lantai bawah dipergunakan untuk kegiatan keagamaan, seperti belajar-mengajar, berdiskusi, dsb. Tembok candi ini juga dilapisi dengan vajralepa (brajalepa), lapisan pelindung yang juga didapati di dinding-dinding Candi Kalasan.
textTranslated: Sari Temple was originally a two or even three storey building. The upper floor was previously used to store items for religious purposes, while the lower floor was used for religious activities, such as teaching and learning, discussions, etc. The walls of this temple are also covered with vajralepa (brajalepa), a protective layer that is also found on the walls of Kalasan Temple.
title: Sari Temple

text:
Candi Sari merupakan salah satu candi Buddha yang indah. Keindahan candi ini bisa dilihat dari arsitekturnya dan dekorasi pahatannya. Apalagi ketika ditambahkan bajralepa. Saat terkena sinar matahari terlihat berkilauan.

Menurut sejarahnya, Candi Sari dibangun oleh Rakai Panangkaran pada abad ketujuh. Raja Mataram Kuno ini membangun candi untuk para biksu. Dan memang, candi ini tidak digunakan sebagai kuil pemujaan. Namun tempat para biksu belajar, berdiskusi dan bertapa. Ada pendapat bahwa kata "sari" ini berasal dari kata "sare" atau tidur. Sehingga tempat tinggal biksu ini disebut candi Sari.

Candi ini selesai direstorasi setelah sempat rusak tak terawat. Arkeolog Belanda A.J Bernet Kempers memulai usah ini pada tahun 1929. Walaupun ada beberapa bagian yang sudah rusak/hilang namun keindahan Candi Sari dapat kita nikmati sampai sekarang. Semoga Candi Sari tetap lestari sebagai warisan sejarah anak cucu kita di masa mendatang.
textTranslated:
Sari Temple is a beautiful Buddhist temple. The beauty of this temple can be seen from its architecture and carved decorations. Especially when you add bajralepa. When exposed to sunlight it looks sparkling.

According to history, Sari Temple was built by Rakai Panangkaran in the seventh century. This ancient Mataram king built a temple for the monks. And indeed, this temple is not used as a shrine of worship. But it is a place for monks to study, discuss and meditate. There is an opinion that the word "sari" comes from the word "sare" or sleep. So the place where this monk lives is called Sari temple.

This temple has been restored after being damaged beyond repair. Dutch archaeologist A.J Bernet Kempers started this business in 1929. Even though some parts have been damaged/lost, we can enjoy the beauty of Sari Temple to this day. We hope that Sari Temple will remain as a historical legacy for our children and grandchildren in the future.
title: Sari Temple

name: doni Hari
text:
Candi selo griyo terletak di windusari  magelang. Tepatnya  di lereng gunung/bukit giyanti magelang. Akses jalan ke lokasi mobil sangat terbatas, sempit dan menanjak.    Mobil hanya bisa parkir di pemukiman penduduk yang berjarak 1,5 km dari lokasi candi. Tempat parkir pun terbatas, mungkin hanya bisa muat sekitar 6 mobil kecil. Tidak ada tempat parkir resmi dan petugas parkir. Ada hanya diminta memasukkan sumbangan dalam kotak yang disediakan. Kendaraan yang lebih besar tidak bisa masuk ke pemukiman tersebut. Selanjutnya akses ke lokasi hanya bisa ditempuh dengan sepeda motor atau berjalan kaki. Jalan sepeda motor pun sangat sempit. Lokasi candi berada di ketinggian dan terpisah jauh dari pekukiman. Tiket masuk per orang rp 7.000, pada hari hari biasa bukan hari libur tidak ada warung makan dan jajanan di sekitar lokasi candi. Tapi ada warung kelontong sederhana didekat pemukiman penduduk.
Kondisi candi sendiri sudah mengalami pemugaran. Beberapa kepala patung dan bangunan candi mengalami perusakan.
Kondisi sekitar masih asri. Menyusuri jalan setapak sepanjang perbukitan dimana pemandangan sawah dan lembah sangat menawan. Udara di lokasi masih segar karena belum banyak kendaraan bermotor yang bisa mengakses lokasi.
Kondisi taman candi cukup terawat dan nyaman. Namun demikian sarana pendukungnya belum memadai seperti toilet, tempat berteduh.
Disarankan datang pagi hari karena udara masih segar.
Sore hari sering turun kabut dan hujan. Sebaiknya membawa bekal minum dan makanan sendiri dan hindari sampah untuk pelestarian lingkungan.
textTranslated:
Selo Griyo Temple is located in Windusari, Magelang. Precisely on the slopes of the Giyanti Magelang mountain/hill. Road access to the car location is very limited, narrow and uphill.    Cars can only be parked in residential areas which are 1.5 km from the temple location. Parking space is limited, perhaps only able to fit around 6 small cars. There are no official parking lots and no parking attendants. You are only asked to enter donations in the box provided. Larger vehicles cannot enter the settlement. Furthermore, access to the location can only be reached by motorbike or on foot. The motorbike road is also very narrow. The location of the temple is at a height and far away from the settlement. Entrance ticket per person is IDR 7,000, on weekdays, not holidays, there are no food stalls and snacks around the temple location. But there are simple grocery stalls near residential areas.
The condition of the temple itself has undergone restoration. Several statue heads and temple buildings were damaged.
The surrounding conditions are still beautiful. Follow the path along the hills where the views of the rice fields and valleys are very charming. The air at the location is still fresh because not many motorized vehicles can access the location.
The condition of the temple gardens is quite well maintained and comfortable. However, the supporting facilities are inadequate, such as toilets and shelter.
It is recommended to come in the morning because the air is still fresh.
In the afternoon there is often fog and rain. It's best to bring your own drinks and food and avoid trash to preserve the environment.
title: Selogriyo Temple

text:

Dari per 3 an menuju candi sekitar 2,5 Km.
Jalan masuk cukup untuk 1 mobil, melewati rumah penduduk. Jalan nanjak terus kadang agak tajam.

textTranslated:
Can be reached via Windusari or Bandongan.
From Per 3 to the temple about 2.5 km.
The driveway is large enough for 1 car, past residents' houses. The road continues to climb, sometimes it's a bit sharp.
At the end of people's houses, there is only a footpath but it has been paved. The journey is quite far, about 600 meters further.

text: Situs purbakala yg berada di Temanggung ini diduga merupakan kompleks perkampungan kuno era Mataram yg terkubur akibat erupsi Gunung Sindoro. Terdapat beberapa temuan peninggalan seperti candi, struktur tembok, saluran air, struktur jalan dan pertirtaan. Situs ini masih tahap dalam tahap konservasi dan belum selesai. Tiket masuknya gratis, hanya perlu laporan dg penjaga. Selain nilai historis yg terkandung, letaknya yg berada di lereng gunung menjadikannya sering jadi jujugan muda-mudi yg sedang berplesiran. Akses menuju kesini sudah bagus, telah terpasang papan penunjuk arah.
textTranslated: This ancient site in Temanggung is thought to be an ancient Mataram era village complex that was buried due to the eruption of Mount Sindoro. There are several heritage finds such as temples, wall structures, water channels, road structures and tirtaan. This site is still in the conservation stage and has not been completed. The entrance ticket is free, you only need to report to the guard. Apart from the historical value it contains, its location on the slopes of a mountain makes it a frequent destination for young people who are on holiday. Access to get here is good, direction signs have been installed.

name: Keperluan Penelitian
street: Jl. Candisari Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.107
text:
Candi Sari merupakan situs peninggalan Buddha. Diperkirakan dulu merupakan asrama atau biara bagi biarawan Buddha. Bangunan Candi Sari merupakan candi tunggal tidak ada bangunan lain disekitarnya. Candi ini sangat dekat dari Candi Kalasan dan berada 50 meter dari Jalan Utama Jogja-Solo.

Tiket masuk Rp. 6.000, ada tempat parkir di depan candi dan toilet di pos penjaga.

Didalam candi terdapat relung berkamar-kamar namun tidak terdapat arca di dalamnya, kemungkinan dulu berlantai dua dengan bahan kayu sebagai pemisahnya.

Yang unik dari candi ini, masih nampak ada warna kekuningan pada ukiran di dinding candi yang merupakan lapisan Bajralepa.
textTranslated:
Sari Temple is a Buddhist heritage site. It is thought that it used to be a dormitory or monastery for Buddhist monks. The Sari Temple building is a single temple with no other buildings around it. This temple is very close to Kalasan Temple and is 50 meters from the Main Road Jogja-Solo.

Entrance ticket Rp. 6,000, there is a parking lot in front of the temple and toilets at the guard post.

Inside the temple there are niches with rooms but there are no statues in them, perhaps it used to have two floors with wood as a divider.

What is unique about this temple is that there is still a yellowish color in the carvings on the walls of the temple which is the Bajralepa layer.
title: Sari Temple

address: Jl. Candisari Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.107, Bendan, Tirtomartani, Kec. Kalasan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia

text:

Bangunan sebenarnya berupa dua lantai, bisa dilihat dari penampakan jendelanya yang berada di atas dan bawah.

Candi Sari ini masih berhubungan dengan candi Budha lainnya yang lokasinya berdekatan, yaitu Candi Kalasan. Kalo Candi Kalasan merupakan tempat ibadahnya, Candi Sari merupakan semacam asrama atau tempat tinggal para biksu-nya.
textTranslated:
The first time you visited this Buddhist temple, what came to mind was that it was beautiful and majestic. Even though there is only one temple and its size is not that big, the temple is really beautiful.

The building is actually two floors, you can see from the appearance of the windows at the top and bottom.

Sari Temple is still connected to another Buddhist temple which is located nearby, namely Kalasan Temple. If Kalasan Temple is a place of worship, Sari Temple is a kind of dormitory or residence for the monks.

text: Candi Sari hanya sekitar 200 meter dari jalan raya solo Yogya lewat gang Yam goreng kalasan. Disebut juga Candi Bendah merupaka Candhi Budha abad 8 dari kerajaan Medang. Terdapat 9 stupa diatas yang mirip dengan bentuk di Borobudur. Candi ini mirip dengan Candi Plaosan sebagai tempat pertapaan atau vihara. Dibangun sejaman dengan Candi Kalasan tetapi pagar batunya sudah tidak ada. Arca dan beberapa bagian hilang termasuk kelengkapan bilik didalamnya. Dipugar pertama tahun 1930 dan tahun 2003 dilakukan rehab. Candi ini di tengah pemukiman warga dan berjarak dekat dengan Sambisari serta diseberang jalan Candi Kalasan. #literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter @galih.wib
textTranslated: Sari Temple is only about 200 meters from the Solo Yogya highway via the Kalasan fried yam alley. Also called Bendah Temple, it is an 8th century Buddhist temple from the Medang kingdom. There are 9 stupas above which are similar to the shape at Borobudur. This temple is similar to Plaosan Temple as a hermitage or monastery. It was built at the same time as Kalasan Temple, but the stone fence is no longer there. The statue and several parts are missing, including the completeness of the room inside. It was first restored in 1930 and in 2003 it was renovated. This temple is in the middle of a residential area and is close to Sambisari and across the street from Kalasan Temple. #literasyikgalih #kilasdocumenter @galih.wib
title: Sari Temple

Situs yang dapat dilihat saat ini berupa jalan kuno, pagar, Yoni, pondasi, petirtaan, kayu, arang padi dan beberapa artefak dari masa Hindu dan mungkin masa neolitik ( temuan batu pipisan ). Situs yang menarik untuk dikunjungi , terutama jika dijelaskan oleh guide yang mengerti temuan-temuan dari situs ini.
textTranslated: Settlement site from the ancient Mataram kingdom era and the prehistoric (neolithic) period. The sites that can be seen today include ancient roads, fences, Yoni, foundations, lightning, wood, rice charcoal and several artifacts from the Hindu period and possibly the Neolithic period (pisan stone finds). An interesting site to visit, especially if explained by a guide who understands the findings of this site.

name: Pandawa 24Jam Digital Printing
text: Situs Liyangan yang dianggap merupakan peninggalan Kerajaan Mataram Kuno ini pada awalnya ditemukan oleh Amin Rahayu pada tahun 1991. Pada tahun 1991 Amin Rahayu dalam kertas kerja atau karya tulisnya menyebut situs liyangan dengan Pusat Kadipaten Bumisari. Cuma pada awalnya orang2 belum pada percaya, maklum waktu itu penemu masih duduk di bangku SMA kelas II mau naik kelas III. Baru pada tahun 2007 ketika Amin Rahayu menjadi PNS di Departemen Kebudayaan dan Pariwisata serta kakak kandungnya (Imbuh Sutrisman) mencalokan diri sebagai CAKADES baru ia bisa sosialisasi (istilahnya pura-pura kampanye)... sayang kakaknya kalah...dan akhirnya daerah yang sudah terlanjur disebut itu diserbu ramai-ramai oleh para penambang pasir dan terbukti adanya semua peninggalan itu..... Selamat... semoga semakin maju dan bermanfaat...
textTranslated: The Liyangan site, which is considered to be a relic of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom, was originally discovered by Amin Rahayu in 1991. In 1991, Amin Rahayu in his working paper or written work called the Liyangan site the Center for the Duchy of Bumisari. However, at first people didn't believe it, because at that time the inventor was still in class II of high school and was going to class III. It was only in 2007 when Amin Rahayu became a civil servant at the Ministry of Culture and Tourism and his older brother (Imbuh Sutrisman) nominated himself as CAKADES that he was able to socialize (the term is pretending to campaign)... unfortunately his older brother lost... and in the end the area had already been established. It was already said that it was heavily invaded by sand miners and it was proven that all the relics existed..... Congratulations... I hope it will be more advanced and useful...

Bukti di zaman pra sejarah telah ada sebuah eksistensi masyarakat sosial dg segenap peradabannya yaitu di sini,di lingkaran gunung tengah bagian Jawa. Dan ternyata pernah ada sebuah kehidupan yg dinamis sebagai sentral dari pemerintahan kejayaan wangsa-wangsa penguasa "Mataram kuno" saat itu.
Sekarang kita tunggu apa yg terbaik yg bisa di lakukan agar tempat ini menjadi sebuah destinasi wisata yg bersifat edukatif.
Halloo...apakabar pihak-pihak yg berwenang?,...kami (Rakyat) menunggumu..
textTranslated:
Very familiar with this place.
Now what is needed is real action to manage this place. It's not like it's half-hearted.
Evidence that in prehistoric times there was the existence of a social society with all its civilization, namely here, in the middle mountain circle of Java. And it turns out that there was once a dynamic life as the center of the glorious government of the ruling dynasties of "ancient Mataram" at that time.
Now we are waiting for what best can be done to make this place an educational tourist destination.
Hello...how are the authorities?...we (the people) are waiting for you...

name: furqon zi gogon
text:
Candi selogriyo adalah suatu tujuan wisata yang amat mempesona. Terletak di kaki bukit condong ,sebelah utara bukit giyanti dan sebelah selatan bukit bakalan ,merupakan perbukitan yang menawan untuk dikunjungi. Candi selogriyo merupakan wilayah dari Desa Kembangkuning dan untuk sampai tujuan, bisa dilalui dengan naik sepeda motor. Apabila ingin naik mobil pribadi,hanya bisa parkir di desa campurjo. Jarak dari aspal jalan  kabupaten sekitar 2.5 km. Tak usah kuatir karena motor bisa sampai dibawah pelataran candi dan tempat parkir sudah disediakan. Namun bila ingin naik ojek,di dusun campurjo sudah siaga para tukang ojek yang melayani dengan ramah.
Tak perlu kuatir akan tersesat menuju candi selogriyo mengingat jalurnya hanya satu saja. Candi ini sudah dipugar beberapa kali dan semakin menunjukkan keindahannya karena fasilitas taman sudah diperbaiki,sudah ditambah aneka tanaman dan menjadi semakin rapi dengan tangga yang dibuat klasik. Pemandangan sejuk akan didapat jika suasana sedikit mendung dan semakin kental rasa romantisme manakala hujan rintik mengguyur menambah memori indah bagi para pelancong. Pelancong yang datang bukan hanya dari lokal atau turis domestik,tetapi banyak kunjungan turis mancanegara karena sudah terjalin kerjasama dengan pihak wisata Borobudur. Pada hari minggu akan kelihatan ramai sedangkan hari biasa cuma beberapa pengunjung. Di bulan tertentu sudah diprogram untuk kegiatan merti dusun dan penampilan kesenian tradisional yang menambah pekatnya pelestarian budaya jawa nan eksotik. Tak pelak jika banyak acara pre wedding dan video shooting untuk klip musik dihelat di sini. Bagi para pendaki gunung,nikmati puncak gunung condong yang terlihat mirip piramida ini.
textTranslated:
Selogriyo Temple is a very enchanting tourist destination. Located at the foot of Leaning Hill, to the north of Giyanti Hill and to the south of Bakalan Hill, these are charming hills to visit. Selogriyo Temple is an area of ​​Kembangkuning Village and to reach its destination, it can be reached by motorbike. If you want to take a private car, you can only park in Campurjo village. The distance from the asphalt district road is around 2.5 km. No need to worry because motorbikes can reach below the temple grounds and parking is provided. However, if you want to take a motorbike taxi, in Campurjo hamlet the motorbike taxi drivers are ready to serve you in a friendly manner.
No need to worry about getting lost on the way to Selogriyo Temple considering there is only one route. This temple has been restored several times and is increasingly showing its beauty because the garden facilities have been improved, various plants have been added and it has become neater with classic stairs. You will get a cool view if the atmosphere is a little cloudy and the feeling of romance will become thicker when light rain falls, adding beautiful memories for travelers. Travelers who come are not only local or domestic tourists, but many foreign tourists visit because there has been cooperation with Borobudur tourism. On Sundays it will look busy, while on weekdays there are only a few visitors. In certain months, it is programmed for merti dusun activities and traditional arts performances which add to the concentration of preserving exotic Javanese culture. Inevitably, many pre-wedding events and video shooting for music clips are held here. For mountain climbers, enjoy this sloping mountain peak that looks like a pyramid.
title: Selogriyo Temple

Rekomendasi buat kalian karena bisa sekaligus beribadah (untuk muslim), kulineran, dan wisata sejarah budaya.
textTranslated:
Coincidentally, I was able to stop here because it was time for Maghrib prayers, which is not far from the colorful dome mosque, which is 150 m away. To enter the temple you only need to pay 10k for domestic tourists and 20k for international tourists.

In this place there is also a culinary tour of kalasan fried chicken, one of which is RM Mbok Mberek.

Recommended for you because you can do worship (for Muslims), culinary delights and cultural history tourism at the same time.

text:
Candi nya bagus dan terawat, candi ini mirip dengan candi kalasan dan hampir mirip juga dengan candi banyunibo. Menurut perkiraan candi ini dibangun pada abad ke- 8 M, yaitu pada masa pemerintahan Rakai Panangkaran. Dalam Prasasti Kalasan diterangkan bahwa para penasehat keagamaan Wangsa Syailendra telah menyarankan agar Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana, yang diperkirakan adalah Rakai Panangkaran, mendirikan bangunan suci untuk memuja Dewi Tara dan sebuah biara untuk para pendeta Buddha.
Lokasi candi ini berada di Desa Bendan, Kelurahan Tirtamartani, Kecamatan Kalasan, Kabupaten Sleman, Yogyakarta
textTranslated:
The temple is nice and well maintained, this temple is similar to Kalasan temple and almost similar to Banyunibo temple. According to estimates, this temple was built in the 8th century AD, namely during the reign of Rakai Panangkaran. In the Kalasan Inscription, it is explained that the religious advisors of the Syailendra dynasty had suggested that Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana, who is thought to be Rakai Panangkaran, build a sacred building to worship the Goddess Tara and a monastery for Buddhist priests.
The location of this temple is in Bendan Village, Tirtamartani Village, Kalasan District, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta
title: Sari Temple

Berlokasi di Tirtomartani, Kalasan, Sleman, candi yang gak terlalu besar ini masih berdiri kokoh dan cukup terawat.

Yang menarik, warga kampung di sekitar sini buka usaha ayam goreng Kalasan. Hampir tiap gang ada warung ayam kalasan. Bahkan jarak antarwarung hanya selisih 2 atau 3 rumah...

textTranslated:
Sari Temple is proof of the glorious past of Indonesian architecture.

Located in Tirtomartani, Kalasan, Sleman, this not too big temple still stands strong and is quite well maintained.

What's interesting is that the villagers around here have opened a Kalasan fried chicken business. Almost every alley has a kalasan chicken stall. Even the distance between stalls is only 2 or 3 houses...
Who are the buyers... I'm curious, because when I came here it was still Eid and Covid-19 conditions, so the stalls were still closed.

textTranslated:
Umbul temple bathing tourist spot
From the main road of Secang-Grabag, we still have to pass through the entrance road which is a connecting road between villages.  We will pass through vast rice fields on either side of the road we are passing.  It's quite far from the main road to this tourist spot
In this place, we can enjoy warm water baths in a pool whose architecture is all made of rocks.  Around the pool, we can also enjoy the neatly arranged gardens, there is also a gazebo there
There is a bathroom, but the bathroom is less comfortable and not clean.  There is also a canteen there

name: Niluh Sonya
text:
Situs bersejarah yg diperkirakan dari zaman tahun 800 an masehi, masa dimana kakek dan nenek buyut kita belum lahir. Ada 2 kolam rendam dengan air hangat suam-suam kuku, yang satu lebih dalam daripada lainnya.

Tempatnya tidak begitu jauh dari jalan raya semarang - magelang. Jalan sudah aspal mulus melewati pedesaan.
Tempat parkir cukup luas. Ada beberapa pendopo untuk duduk santai.
Kamar mandi dan ruang bilas cukup tersedia.
Kebersihan lingkungan sekitar kolam cukup terjaga meski masih perlu ditingkatkan lagi.
Air kolam berwarna hijau karena lumut yang menempel. Harus hati-hati saat menapak tangga turun kolam, bisa terpeleset.

Wifi gratis dari pemda magelang tersedia juga.
Ada warung kecil menjajakan nasi goreng, soto, aneka indomie dan jajanan lain.
Di seberangnya ada warung yang menjual celana pendek dan pelampung untuk berenang, ada juga warung makan kecil.

Tiket masuknya rp 6 rb per orang,parkir mobil rp5 rb.
Saat liburan kemarin tanggal 7 juli 2023 lumayan ada beberapa pengunjung namun tidak terlalu ramai (tidak sampai 20 orang).
textTranslated:
A historical site that is thought to date back to the 800s AD, a time when our great-grandparents and grandfathers were not yet born. There are 2 wading pools with lukewarm water, one deeper than the other.

The place is not too far from the Semarang - Magelang highway. The road is smooth asphalt through the countryside.
The parking lot is quite spacious. There are several pavilions to sit and relax.
There are enough bathrooms and toilets available.
The cleanliness of the environment around the pool is quite well maintained although it still needs to be improved.
The pool water is green because of the moss attached to it. You have to be careful when walking down the stairs to the pool, you could slip.

Free wifi from the Magelang regional government is also available.
There are small stalls selling fried rice, soto, various indomie and other snacks.
Opposite there is a stall selling shorts and buoys for swimming, there is also a small food stall.

The entrance ticket is IDR 6 thousand per person, car parking is IDR 5 thousand.
During the last holiday, July 7 2023, there were quite a few visitors but it wasn't too busy (not up to 20 people).

text:
Situs candi sambisari
Candi yang merupakan salah satu tempat bersejarah, jadi perlu lah kita sebagai anak muda melestarikannya.
Arenya cukup luas, pemandangannya bagus. Dari jauh kelihatan pucuk candinya saja, jadi kalau mau lihat harus mendekat, karna candinya berada di bawah.
Ada 4 candi disana, tapi yg tiga tidak utuh, hanya satu saja yg utuh.
Biaya masuknya pun murah, cukup dengan uang Rp. 5000,- untuk tourist lokal.
Cukup sepi, mungkin karena di hari kerja pas kesananya.
Bolehlah kita sebagai generasi penerus buat melestarikan kekayaan yang dimiliki Indonesia.
Jasmerah,  jangan sekali kali melupan sejarah. Salam budaya.
textTranslated:
Sambisari temple site
The temple is a historical place, so we as young people need to preserve it.
The area is quite large, the view is good. From a distance you can only see the top of the temple, so if you want to see it you have to get closer, because the temple is at the bottom.
There are 4 temples there, but three of them are not intact, only one is intact.
The entry fee is also cheap, just Rp. 5000,- for local tourists.
It's quite quiet, maybe because it's right there on weekdays.
May we as the next generation preserve the wealth that Indonesia has.
Jasmerah, never forget history. Cultural greetings.

The last option seems to have to be accompanied by excellent physical condition, because the road is hilly and quite long, but the views offered are truly amazing. At the time there was restoration work being carried out here. On several parts of the temple walls there are statues, most of which are without heads, such as the Ganesha statue. Apart from the temple, there is also a pentirtaan site here. The atmosphere here is very cool, quiet. A suitable place to refresh the mind. HTM 7,500, toilets and a stall are available. Access here from the city of Magelang is also good.

name: Tyas Rudatin
text:
Candi yg tersembunyi diantara rimbunnya hutan dn hijaunya persawahan. Tempat yg indah dn sunyi. Dulu adalah tempat pertapaan untuk memdekatkan diri pada Sang Pencipta. Termasuk dlm gugusan Candi Hindu.
Masih berada di kawasan kabupaten Magelang yg tersohor dgn candi Borobudurnya yg megah.
Namun Candi Selogriyo seperti luput dr kunjungan krn akses yg hrs ditempuh masih seadanya. Dan belum ada perbaikan dibangunnya infrastruktur jalan yg memadai untuk sampai lokasi Candi. Sungguh suatu keindahan tersembunyi seolah tak terjamah.
Akses ke sana dr ujung desa Kembang Kuning hanya ada ojek motor pp dgn tarif 40 ribu pulang pergi. Kita akan ditungguin untuk diantar pulang ke tmpt kendaraan kt terparkir. Semua dikelola oleh Desa setempat. Dengan tiket masuk hanya 3 ribu rupiah. Sangat terjangkau dgn indah dn damainya suasana yg didapat. Hanya akses kesana sj yg sulit. Wl dgn ojek motor jagan bayangkan jalan mulus. Krn hrs melewati pematang sawah dn saluran pengairan. Bahkan sy hampir terjatuh dr gonjengan motor, krn motor oleng jalanan berlumpur krn gerimis dtng.
Semoga Pemerintah dn aparat Desa lebih bisa memberikan akses jalan yg lebih baik . Agar bs lbh memberdayakan potensi wisata yg ada. Sehingga akan bs menggeliatkan ekonomi rakyat yg terkait.
textTranslated:
The temple is hidden among the lush forests and green rice fields. Beautiful and quiet place. In the past, it was a place of hermitage to get closer to the Creator. Included in the Hindu Temple group.
Still in the Magelang district area which is famous for its magnificent Borobudur temple.
However, Selogriyo Temple seems to escape visits because the access that must be taken is still limited. And there has been no improvement in the construction of adequate road infrastructure to reach the temple location. It's a hidden beauty that seems untouchable.
Access to there from the end of Kembang Kuning village only has a return motorbike taxi with a fare of 40 thousand round trip. We will be waiting for you to be taken home to the place where your vehicle is parked. All managed by the local village. With an entrance ticket of only 3 thousand rupiah. Very affordable with a beautiful and peaceful atmosphere. Only access there is difficult. Even with a motorbike taxi, don't imagine smooth roads. Because it has to pass through rice fields and irrigation channels. In fact, I almost fell off the motorbike, because the motorbike swerved on the muddy road because of the drizzle.
Hopefully the government and village officials can provide better road access. So that we can further exploit the existing tourism potential. So it will be able to stimulate the economy of the people involved.
